# Railway Environment Variables Template

# Copy this template and fill in your actual values in the Railway dashboard
# Go to: Your Project → Variables → Add Variables

# ======================
# REQUIRED VARIABLES
# ======================

# Database Password (from your Supabase/PostgreSQL database)
DB_PASSWORD=your-actual-database-password-here

# Google OAuth Credentials (from Google Cloud Console)
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=GOCSPX-your-google-client-secret

# JWT Secret (generate a strong random key, minimum 256 bits)
# You can generate one with: openssl rand -base64 32
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secure-jwt-secret-key-minimum-256-bits-long

# ======================
# OPTIONAL VARIABLES
# (Railway may auto-inject some, or use defaults from application.properties)
# ======================

# Port (Railway auto-assigns this, but you can override)
# PORT=8080

# Database URL (if different from default)
# DATABASE_URL=jdbc:postgresql://your-db-host:5432/postgres

# Database Username (if different from default)
# DB_USERNAME=postgres.ujbskgmuoteogvskegnd

# CORS Allowed Origins (comma-separated, add your frontend URLs)
# Example: https://your-frontend.vercel.app,http://localhost:8081
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:8081,https://your-frontend-url-here.com

# OAuth Redirect URI (must match your Railway app URL)
# Update this after Railway assigns your URL
# OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=https://your-app-name.up.railway.app/login/oauth2/code/google

# ======================
# STEPS TO CONFIGURE
# ======================

# 1. Go to Railway Dashboard → Your Project → Variables
# 2. Click "Add Variable" or "Raw Editor"
# 3. Copy-paste the required variables above (without # comments)
# 4. Fill in actual values
# 5. Click "Deploy" or changes will auto-deploy

# ======================
# GOOGLE OAUTH SETUP
# ======================

# After Railway deploys your app:
# 1. Note your Railway app URL (e.g., https://your-app.up.railway.app)
# 2. Go to Google Cloud Console → Credentials
# 3. Edit your OAuth 2.0 Client ID
# 4. Add Authorized Redirect URI:
#    https://your-app.up.railway.app/login/oauth2/code/google
# 5. Save changes
# 6. Update OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI variable in Railway (optional, for clarity)

# ======================
# TESTING
# ======================

# Local testing with Railway environment:
# 1. Create a .env file (DO NOT COMMIT TO GIT)
# 2. Add these variables
# 3. Use Railway CLI: railway run ./gradlew bootRun

